    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">328 Mickle street</name>
                    <name type="place">Camden New Jersey<ptr target="hsw.00763_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1884-10-05">October 5 1884<ptr target="hsw.00763_n2"/></date>
                </dateline>
            </opener> 
            <p>I knew Reuben Farwell as a first-class soldier (it was in
                1863 or '64)<ptr target="hsw.00763_n3"/> of a Michigan Regiment&#8212;he was in Ward
                A, Armory Square Hospital, Dr Bliss Superintendent<ptr target="loc.00876_n3"
                />&#8212;I was with him off &amp; on some months &amp; remember the case perfectly
                well. He had a very bad foot wound, &amp; I should judge it something that would
                deteriorate his health &amp; more or less incapacitate him through life
                afterward&#8212;till his death&#8212;&amp; even toward that event&#8212;which as I
                understand occurred about a year ago. </p>
            <p> I strongly recommend the granting a pension to his widow Ann E. Farwell.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Very respectfully,</salute>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
